fields.physical_description:
1. screen card frame covered with paper printed in colours to show a theatrical setting with Chinese characters and decoration together with red curtains. The screen itself is white glazed cotton. The sides of the frame are covered with black paper. There is some wear
on the paper edges and foxing on the cotton. 11½ x 14½ x 1 3/4in 
*2+- silhouettes; card covered with black paper highlighted with white lines; some have small holes so light will be pass through. Assorted figures and characters; including animals. 
*Group from the Molière play 'Malade Imaginaire (Jean-Baptiste
Poquelin; 1622-1673) He wrote plays for the court of Louis XIV.

137. box lid; card covered with paper printed in colours to show a floral decoration around the label; and in blue and white to show Chinese scene rather like the Willow pattern around the edges. The label is a lithograph; in colour; to show an indoor scene of people watching a shadow theatre performance. They look working class and the scene includes children. The title is printed in black across the top. It is signed in lower left corner and along bottom edge are the printers details. In the top left corner is an oval label giving the retailer's name JULES DECRE NANTES/6 BASSE GRANDE/and above ARTICLES DE MENAGE JOUETS ET JEUX 
138. box base; card covered with printed paper around edge showing the Chinese scenes; shaped with inner panel and outer lip; painted gold to hold the top; bottom covered with blue paper

fields.history_note:
References: bought June 2, 1993, Lot 281

Probably all the characters are from the play Malade Imaginaire which included a Polichinelle scene and dancers. See Penguin Classics translation by John Wood; 1st published 1959 - 'Molière the Misanthrope and Other Plays'.

Price: £280.00 + VAT; £378.00
